{"/service/ndnp/ndhi/batch_ndhi_hebron_ver01/data/sn85042414/0029586347A/1921031701/0717.xml":{"full_text":"if-S\nE*lr\n-'r\nISts\nlK\nlifti\n,4j:^\niKi'lxi\n1\n}'1\u2022\u2022]\nf'i\nrib-,*\n)m!\ni1\nLi\n4-\nw-\nPAGE TWELVE.\nftW\nCOMPLETE LINE\nOF MERCHANDISE\nSpring Opening Week Dis\nplay is Unusual, and At\ntracts Attention.\nThe striking window displays which\nhave featured Spring Opening week at\nthe Benner Begg establishment,\nhave given the hundreds of persona\nwho stopped to admire them just an\ninkling of what ^in attractive stock of\nmerchandise is to be found within.\nAgainst a background that is artis\ntically colored and designed, some of\nthe choicest offerings from the vari\nous departments have been arranged,\nand the windows are perhaps the\nmost striking that have been seen\nhere in several seasons.\nN. G. Brnner, with his son, Robert\nBenner, returned here recently from\na trip to New York, and other east\nern centers, where they purchased\ntheir spring stock for the Benner\nBegg store. They brought back some\nof the most attractive garments for\nthe women's ready-to-wear depart\nment that they could find among the\nreason's offerings, and they also\nbrought with them the optimism an4\nencouragement that h^s been estab\nlished in connection with the business\noutlook for the coming season.\nThe attitude of confidence in the\nbusiness outlook has extended from\nthe manufacturer and dealer to the\nbuyer, according to N. G. Benner, and\nprospects are good for a comfortable\nand successful season, he believes. He\nsucceeded in getting very complete\nlines of merchandise for the various\ndepartments of his store, ^nd has pre\npared ifpr a big volume of business.\nThe New Wraps.\nThe woman who goes shopping just\nat this tirile will center her interest,\nprobably, ahput the things for the\nearly bpring '\"costume\u2014including a\nsuit, or a coat, and one of the smart\nnew frocks. Then for the other ac\ncessories\u2014a hat, shoes, gloves, blouse\nand in fact of the things that the\nwell-dressed Woman needs to complete\nher costume, may be found at Ben\nner Beggs'.\nPerhaps the most interesting of the\nthings that this season is bringing to\nfeminine fashion are the new wraps\n\u2014dolman-like, with neither belts nor\nbuttons, and in which fair damsels\nmay literally \"wrap\" themselves.\nBenner Begg's are showing a large\nassortment of these in the new col\nors, new lines, and with all of the new\nfeatures. Some of the most striking\nof these are in the Florizelle and\nChamoistype cloths soft, rather\nheavy materials that seem to have\nbeen made just for the jiew wraps.\nThe capes, or coats, which ever one\nmay prefer to cvi.ll them, are in the\nnew shades\u2014gravel, greys.\nand b-ue, and one of the very hand\nsome coats that may be seen by the\nshopper at Benner Begg's is in a\ncombination of satin and Val de\ncygne, with stitched trimming. There\nalso is another distinctive coat in\nblack\nF,atin,\nwith touches of buff\nchamoistyne, and puffings of the satin.\nThis is rather more for dressy wear.\nIn addition to the capes, there are\nsome of the coats in more tailored\nstyle, for the woman who does not\ncare for the loose styles.\nSmart Salts.\nSuits offer a wide range of choice,\nfrom the strictly tailored models to\nthe jaunty little short box coats, \u00a3.nd\nthe belted models with their scalloped\nedges. The cape backs also have a\nplace among the suits, and there is a\nplenty of embroidery, stitching and\nBashes to give distinction to the suit.\nBlue are most in demand here for the\nsuit this spring, and some of the\nhandsomest models are in this staple\ncolor, though the new gravel shade,\ngreys and browns are shown.\nIf we stop for a minute to look at\nthe gowns Vhich Benner Begg's\nare' showing we will find a bpwilder\nlng array of taffetas In the bouffant\nand long-waisted styles georgettes\nand satin combinations some lovely\nCanton crepe models in grey a.nd\nbrown, and embroidered silk net over\ntaffeta. Ginghams, voiles and or\ngandies in the fascinating modes also\nhave been p'aced in stock.\nFor the junior miss from 12 to 16\nyears, there are orr^ndy frocks in the\npastel shades, and also some clever\ndesigns in ginghams.\nSeparate skirts in plaid, checks and\nFROM\n\"sr-\nVermont BMjg.\n\u00ab*1 -ttf\nA\n(Continued from page 3.)\nbows \u00bbnd combined with the small\nbunches of many colored flowers are\nmeeting with favor for the early\nspring hat and this manner of hat it\nis found may always be worn at in^\ntervals later in the season with the\nsummer frock.\nThere is no prevailing shape or\ncolor for woman's hat this year, it is\nplainly shown. It is invariably proven\nthat despite a prevailing shape, mi\nl&dy will make an attempt to choose\na shape best fitted to her style of\nbeauty, and Miss Knox in selecting her\nstock this spring has had this idea\nin mind.\nHerald Want Ads Bring Results.\nSUITS MADE TO ORDER\n$27.00\nIT IS NOT TOO LATE -TO GET YOUR\nEASTER SUIT MADE\nWe* will give you real Tailor-Made-3uit, per^f\nfectly fitted to your own build-in Tiew style:\u2014new1'\nin every thread and line the day you put it on and\nit wijl cost you no more when yoij take ipto cqn\nsideration the length of service that you .will re\nceive in wear and shape.\nWE ALSO DO DRY CLEANING'\nAND PRESSING'\nXAIIiOR'\nit\nMade\nTo\nAND UP \"j|\nAGrand\nForks, N. DC\n'L-\nf-\nMB\n\u2022w^sjiM\nConcert Singer Inherits\nHeirloom Robe of Rare Old Lace\nMiss Edok Thomas.\nThis is a new photograph of Miss Edna Thomas, the well-known con\ncert singer. Miss Thomas is at Present the envy of all her feminine as\nsociates, for she has just inherited a robe of rare old French lace. The\npattern of this beautiful fabric was broi/ght into France from Italy early\nin the eighteenth century. The lace -from which the gown was made was\nbought in Paris about fifty years ago and in color is said to be one of the\nmost beautiful specimens of its kind, it has ai commercial valuation of\n$2,000.\n\u2022tripes, made up in the box and knife\npleating for wear with the sweater,\nwhich also may be found here, are\nparticularly smart. Blouses in the\ndelicate new colorings, trimmings and\nstyles have an important place in the\nready-to-wear department.\nComplete lines.\nThere is a shortage of certain ma\nterials which arc much in demand\nnow, notably taffeta\u2014dvilrs have\nfound, and they arc urging patrons to\npurchase materials of this kind early\nin the season. Benner Begg's have\nbeen fortunate in getting a good sup\nply of the popular materials, but the\ndemand is heavy At this time. Migel's\nBilks are handled here, and in this\nline are featured the Moonglo satin,,\nbrowns Fantasie silk, Hindu crepe, and there\nis a complete line of crepe de chftie,\ntaffetati, voiles, organdies and ging\nhams to select from. Skirtings in\nwool plaids are shown in p. variety of\ncolors.\nRibbons for sashes and vestees,\nflouncings. featuring filet nets, new\n(loves, hosiery, lingerie, and a com\nplete shoe department, also are in\ncluded in the Benner Begg stock.\nKnown as \"The Grey Drapery Shop.\"\nA very complete department is de\nToted to materials for draperies and\ncurtains, this department being in\ncharge of John Henderson. Mr. Hen\nderson also has charge of the window\ndisplays.\nHOISETH'S HAS\nCLEVER STYLES\nNORDLUND HAS\nBEEN TAILOR\nFOR MANY YEARS\nN. Nordlund, who ^r some 29 years\nhas had a tailoring establishment ir.\n\"Grand Forks, is prepared this season\nto carry on a particularly large vol\nume of 'business. He has stocked his\nestablishment with a substantial and\nup to date line of materials for men's\nsuits and coats, and believes from In\ndications already manifested, that the\nseason Is to be an encouraging one\nfrom a business viewpoint.\n-All suits turned out of the Nordlund\nshop are strictly made to measure,\nand- that they are built along, correct,\nlines, and are marked Ay the best\nkind of tailoring, is evident from the\nlong and substantial patronage which\nNordlund's has enjoyed for so many\nyears.\nMaterials for the new clothing this\nspring are particularly good, and' Mr.\nNordlund has placed a very large sup\nply of them on his shelves/\nSMARTHATS AT\nTHE KNOX SHOP\n(Sontinued from page 3.)\nKnox states are worn in ali%of the\neastern cities in navy blue, grey and\nall black. The strictly tailored\" woman\ntakes delight in her sifaall sailor\nwhich she wears upon most occasions\nwith her early spring suit, Miss Knox\nhas remarked.\nThe sailorfe arc being shown with\nresulted in the showing of an excep\ntional array of hats fpr early spring\nand summer wear.\nMitzivsailors, chic in style, and\nshowing a variety of trimming, are\nbeing featured largely at the Hoiseth\nshop, and the poke bonnet effects may\nbe seen here in several attractive\ntypes and colors. In view of the fact\nthat this is a season of g&y color Cor\nmillinery, Miss Hoiseth has taken this\ninto account, and the tangerine, j,ade,\ngrey and other leading shades are to\nbe seen in refreshing and individual\nhats for the sunshiny spring days.\nTliere is no need for any woman,\nno matter what her type to go unbe\ncomingly hatted this season, Miss\nHoiseth declares, because the fashion\nfor the spring and4 feummer provides\nfor such a variety of styles and tastes.\nThe broad brimmed hat, the close fit\nting hat, the hat with the narrow\nbrim, the poke shape and the trim\ntailored sailor, all have 'important\nplaces in the spring fashion parade,\nand there is a wide selection In all\nof these styles. Flower hats are good\nthis jseasan, Miss Hoiseth states, and\nshe has been showing some pretty\nmodels -made entirely of flowers.\nThe lace drops around the edges\nof brimmed hats, are seen for the\nspring and veils, full draped, for thd\nsmall h\u00a3.ts are to be found ,in a vari\nety of designs at the\" Hoiseth shop.\nR0UTZAHN HATS\nALWAYS CLEVER\n(Continued from page 3.)\nportunity for providing variety in the\nmillinery display this spring, anil the\nRoutzahn shop, like others that are\nup to date, is offering to itrs patrons a\nnumber of different types. The always\ndependable\" Fisk hat is featured at\nMrs. Routzahp's.\nThe bright colors and\" the shiney\nmaterials which seem to be leading\nthis spring, the alWflower, or feather\nhat, and the models combined of\nstraws and ribbon or silk, are fea\ntures of the stock which certainjy\nshould prove of special interest to the\nfeefore-Easter shopper. The Mitzi\nsailor, without which no millintery\nstock would be complete, has of course\nbeen given due regard by Mrs,\nRoutzahn in selecting 'her 'hat display\nfor the spring, and gome of tub-most\nchic little models In this style which\nhave been brought to Grand\\Forks are\nat the Routzahn shop. I.\nGRAY iS~IN LEAD\nFOR SPRING WEAR\nNew York- costumers say that gray,\nis surely the color fpr American wear\nthis season. Everything-is. done in\ngr^y from, hats ,to shoes. And if the\ncreation is not all in gray then some\npart of it is sure to- be, Blue capes\nllave gray linlngs^or gray colors. Blue^n\nhats have .gray trimmings. Reddish]\ntones of trimming are applied to a\ngray foundation. 'Gray suits aVe the\norder of the day. Gray stockings arc\nworn with VIKk shoes unless' gray\nshoes are used. Always there is eraj}\nsomewhere in the offing and, sinca,\nthere are .many tone* and shades- or\n'this: ona color, every,/prie of every\ncomplexion can find something: in col-i\nof that suits her general makeup..\nKow and again atotOrig the' -newer\nAmerican showings the circular skirt\nis se*n. it is the,, only evidence, we\nhavf\nbt\nany widening, of the'skirt,\nbut when it is .circular i\u00a3 has' the\ngreatest amount of fullness used in\nits making,\n\u2022\u2022{\u2022ii\nL'H\nfi\nFASHION SECTION\u2014GRAND FORKS I HERALD.\n^tore\nThT\nArcomnvKlatjn\nWomen's\nand\nMisses'\nFrocks\n\"C*OR every new fashion^\nits own fabri\u00a3 and gar\nniture. Silk and crepe\nfrocks embroidered in odd\nly, foreign stitching or\nbeaded in jet or bright col\nored beads. Summer\nfrocks for the afternoon or\nthe evening dance. Frocks\nof taffetfa, of Canton crepe,\nof woolen fabrics\u2014sparkle^\nwith the light playing up\non the beading. The sheer\nyouth of'them is irresist\nible.\nNECKWEAR\nNeckwear was never\nmore lovely or more\nin keeping with the\ngladsome spirit of\nspringtime. As it is\nright now it abounds\nwith novel shapes,\ncolors and decora\ntive touches. Vestees\nthat will contribute\na world of distinc\u00ad\ntion to your costume arc here for your\nchoosing.\nVEILS\u2014VEILINGS\nThe new drape veils not only re\nveal but enhance the wearers\nbeauty. The. round and the square\nveils w^h meif conventional pat\nterns are exceedingly smart.\nThey come in henna,' taupe, grey,\nbrown amd navy in various shap\ned meshes.\nThe fine materials of which all\nBenner and Bega shoes are made\n\u2022\u2014the creations of the artist and\nthe skill of the craftsman are the\ncombined elements which unite in\nthe making of all our distinguish\ned styles.\nIntroducing a new and* original\nstyle\u2014The New ariop\u2014fash\nioned in brown kidr suede quar\nters and instep strap to match.\n.Baby Louis heel.\nI ia)\u00ae: r\\-'iy i^?i^F iiai\nENNER BEC/P ENNER BEG\n\u00a3^^JQl JtvrThe\nA Brilliant Display of all That is Newest in\nACCESSORIES OF DRESS AND HOME DECORATIONS\nWHAT IS NEW? What is\n^Smartest in Shoes?\nHow are Clothes Being Made?\nAre Spring Furs anj different? What are the modish colors for Vests and Gloves are\ncolors to harmonize or contrast this Spring? Maybe you are most interested in how to do\nover the sun parlor or the scheme of yotir- new living room.\nThese and countless other queries are best answered by viewing the vivid new displays\npresenting tfie best, the newest and most authentic in style that the new season has to offer.\nAH is in readiness, eyery section, every window and every case has assumed its Spring garb\nand is awaiting ytur close inspection.\nYour Suit in Time for Easter\nOf grey, navy and serge, cord twill, whipcord, poiret twill, are some of the\nvery new, very smart semi-tailored suits\u2014the kind a woman wears and instinc\ntively knows she is well dressed for any day time occasion. Nothing quite\ncomes up to the practicability of such a suit.\nGLOVES\nThe mousquetaire is still the glove\nof the hour. Indeed its popularity this\n'season promises to exceed that of any\nprevious period for not only silk* and\nwool frocks but shits flaunting the\nthree-quarter sleeve makes wearing it\na pleasant necessity. It is shown in\nsilk and kid as are the wrist-length\ngloves.\nCatch the sun in cherry hang\ning\u2014great sprawly patterns in\nglowing colors in cretonnes,\nbright colored silks and velours\nsee& to be in favor for draperies.\nSun parlors and-rooms which\nhave a semi-outdoor character as\nwell ,as alt 6ther -rooms will fittd\ntheir needs beautifully provided\nTHURSDAY,\nStore\nMARCH 17, 19211\nAccommodating\nWomen's\nand\nMisses\nWraps\nTj the cut of the cloth\na or\nwraps dcclare themselves\nSpring 1921. Georgeous\nembroideries trace designs\non neutral-toned chamois\ntync, Florizelle, Duvetyne.\nStill others, simple in line,.\nare of bright hu\u00a3s embroi\ndered or braided in silken\nthreads The number and\nbeauty of the new wraps,\nthe charm and novelty of\ntrimmings at once appeal\n\"to your discriminating\ntaslc.\nHOSIERY\nBeautiful enough\nto do justice to\nthe most attrac\ntive footwear for\nSpring is the new\nsilk hosiery.\nr*x\nirj-ft Hi\ni:\nSt\nUMBRELLAS\nQuaint and stubby for rain or shine\nwith their bracelets of amber and col\nored ivory and their gay colored cov\ners add charm to an article of service.\nRIB3DNS\u2014-SASHES\nA note of color will be found Hi the\nnew ribbons tor spring, elaborate bro\ncades, for the silk band-batja, stripes\ntand plaJds for sashes, dainty ribbons\nfor the underthlngs, are all found\nhere.\nSashes are rampant in the land of\nfashion. Sashes with long dmigHng\ntassels or fringes, be&^s of glass or\ncolored wood' add vivid touches to the\nsimplest of Crocks.\n7\nNow come the new Blouses\u2014\nflower-like in their spring colors\nof airy crepe and georgette&^-fit\ntingly charming to accompany\nnew suits.\nClad in one of these attractive\nblouses a woman may detain her\nwell dressed appearance at all\ntimes Delicate shades as well as\nthe darker color for traveling\nmay be found here.\n'Jv-T\n,1\n-\\*v.\n1","height":"28335","width":"20524"}}
